@The-Dub Sorry for this. Windows doesn't have imagemagick installed by default.

Can you follow the link below to install imagemagick and try again?

http://www.imagemagick.org/script/binary-releases.php

@piiswrong 
The first thing is to support C++ testing. I am working on a project for face recognition. I don't want my clients to see my codes, and they would not always have a python environment on their PC. 

The second thing is personal. I am not very familiar with python. My programming skill only includes C++ and Matlab. Unfortunately, these two languages are not supported by MXNet. Thus, I gave up moving to MXNet. I am glad to see a C++ interface and continue to learn MXNet because your codes are really awesome.
